<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10">

  <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b-2 border-[#FFCF00]">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-normal">About</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-start">

    <div class="space-y-5 text-[#666666] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Ten of Cups Ceramics is a small studio practice rooted in the making of everyday objects.
        The studio is named for the tarot card of the same name — a card associated with contentment,
        gratitude, and the simple pleasures of a life well-lived.
      </p>
      <p>
        All work is wheel-thrown and hand-finished. Glazes are mixed in-house. Each piece is fired
        in a small electric kiln and is intended to be used daily — to hold your coffee, your soup,
        your flowers.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pieces are made in small batches, which means stock is limited. If something sells out and
        you'd like to be notified when it returns, reach out via the contact page.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <img src="/images/about-meryll.jpg" alt="Meryll at a market with her ceramics" class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover" />
      <img src="/images/about-wheel.jpg" alt="Throwing on the pottery wheel" class="w-full rounded-2xl object-cover" />
    </div>

  </div>

</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
